MAT550 | Differential Geometry | http://registrar.princeton.edu/course-offerings/course_details.xml?courseid=012863&term=1152 | instructors:Fernando Codá Santos Cavalcanti Marques description:This is an introductory graduate course covering questions and methods in differential geometry.  As time permits, more specialized topics will be covered as well, including minimal submanifolds, curvature and the topology of manifolds, the equations of geometric analysis and its main applications, and other topics of current interest.
MAT558 | Topics in Conformal and Cauchy-Rieman (C: Recent Developments in Conformal Geometry | http://registrar.princeton.edu/course-offerings/course_details.xml?courseid=012632&term=1152 | instructors:Sun-Yung A. Chang description:This course covers current topics in Conformal and Cauchy-Rieman (CR) Geometry.  More specific topic details are provided when the course is offered.
MAT559 | Topics in Geometry: Conformally covariant operators and their associated Q-curvatures | http://registrar.princeton.edu/course-offerings/course_details.xml?courseid=008121&term=1152 | instructors:Paul C. Yang description:This course covers the following: The CR conformal Laplacian and the scalar curvature equation, the fourth order Paneitz operator on a conformal 4-manifold and the fourth order CR Panietz operator of CR 3-manifold. The positivity property, the CR embedding problem and the CR positive mass theorem and its relation with the d-bar equation, the solution of the CR Yamabe equation, the new operator on the pluriharmonic functions and its associated Q-curvature, the Q-curvature integral and the Burns-Epstein invariant.
MAT579 | Topics in Discrete Mathematics: Graph Minors | http://registrar.princeton.edu/course-offerings/course_details.xml?courseid=012360&term=1152 | instructors:Paul D. Seymour description:This course is a survey of the Graph Minors project of Robertson and the speaker, and some recent extensions. The main topics are graph path-width and tree-width, and extensionsused for the Graph Minors project; some description of how this is used to solve the k vertex-disjoint paths problem in a graph; containment relations for digraphs, and particularly for tournaments; a recent solution of the k vertex-disjoint directed paths problem in tournaments;graph well-quasi-ordering, and tournament well-quasi-ordering.
MAT380 | Probability and Stochastic Systems | http://registrar.princeton.edu/course-offerings/course_details.xml?courseid=007999&term=1152 | instructors:Ramon van Handel description:An introduction to probability and its applications.  Random variables, expectation, independence.  Poisson processes, Markov chains, and Brownian motion.  Stochastic models of queues, population dynamics, and reliability.
MAT306 | Advanced Logic | http://www.princeton.edu/~jburgess | instructors:John P. Burgess description:An introduction to axiomatic set theory, up to the proof of the consistency of the axiom of choice.
